<title>USA: First Nationwide to issue debt for Cal Fed merger.</title>
<headline>First Nationwide to issue debt for Cal Fed merger.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-08-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Nationwide Holdings Inc said it will fund its previously announced $1.2 billion merger agreement with California Federal Bancorp Inc with the issuance of notes, preferred stock and existing cash.</p>
<p>First Nationwide, which is controlled by New York financier Ronald Perelman's MacAndrews &amp; Forbes, said it will issue $525 million in senior subordinated notes and get $145 million in cash from First Gibraltar Holdings, a unit of MacAndrews &amp; Forbes.</p>
<p>First Gibraltar would receive $150 million in liquidation value of perpetual preferred stock of First Nationwide Holdings, the company said.</p>
<p>The balance of the purchase price for Cal Fed would be funded with cash from First Nationwide, the company said.</p>
